 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ucobra102.showPublicProfile?language=EN>cobra102</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/23/02 2:58:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1427.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: re</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> By TzarothFV:<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Most of you know my admittedly close-minded view on names already, but I'll offer up a condensed version: I think that, if your name makes a phrase or it's pornographic or what-have-you, you deserve to get it taken away. You know what you're doing when you create it, so don't whine when someone catches on. </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I don't know if you looked at the Naming Policy lately but phrases per se are no longer forbidden. Offensive, sexual etc phrases are but not simply the process of compound names. After all in many cultures compound names are perfectly normal. Would you say &quot;Danceswithwolves&quot; was not appropriate in a Native American context? It could be equally suited to a barbarian beastlord.<br>
<br>
Since there seems some confusion here is the current (09/23/02) naming policy:<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
The following types of names are inappropriate:.<br>
<br>
Vile, profane, rude, or racist names including common swear words, anatomical references, racial slurs, and homonyms of these words. <br>
<br>
Combinations of words that produce an offensive result (e.g. Hugeaz, Tug Mcgroin). <br>
<br>
Names of religious, occult, or significant historic origin (e.g. Jesus, Allah, Satan, Stalin, Angel, Devil, Demon). <br>
<br>
Trademarked names of products, services, or concepts (e.g. , Marlboro, Sony, Band-Aid). <br>
<br>
Non-fantasy oriented names from popular media. These names can be either fictional (e.g. Rambo, Darthvader) or non-fictional (e.g. Garth Brooks, Pierce Brosnan, Ronald Reagan, Michael Jordan). <br>
<br>
Common words and phrases that would not be found in the place and time setting of the game (e.g. Switchblade, Phaser, Toaster, Sloegin, Anyone). This includes references to drug substances or drug related paraphernalia. (e.g. Ecstacy, Cannibis) <br>
<br>
Proper names from EverQuest (e.g. Rathe, Karana). This also includes the first or last name of any significant EverQuest NPC (e.g. Dorn, Trumpy, Karn). <br>
<br>
Names chosen with the intent or possessed with the effect of harming the reputation of or used to impersonate a Customer or representative of Sony Online Entertainment. <br>
<br>
Names containing titles within them, such as, but not limited to: The, Lord, Lady, Master, King, Knight, Sir, Father (e.g. Sirtallon, Lordeagle, Mothermaggy, Darksister). <br>
<br>
Fantasy-oriented names that are easily recognized from popular existing media (e.g. Merlin, Gandalf, Belgarath, Drizzt, Tanis). <br>
<br>
Names where the combination of the first and last name violate a previous rule. <br>
<br>
For all of the above, misspellings and alternative spellings of the word or words are also unacceptable.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Note that one category is &quot;Common words <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> and phrases</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> that would not be found....&quot; ie implying that common words and phrases that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> would</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> be found are not unacceptable. Again &quot;Combinations of words that produce an offensive result&quot; are forbidden, implying that combinations which do not produce such a result are not.<br>
<br>
You probably gather from this that my own name is indeed a phrase, but one that I feel is perfectly at home in the EQ mileiu. It is the same name that got me invited to an RP guild on another server. On FV it has brought me some compliments and some attacks from RP-police.<br>
<br>
If you look at the above rules there are so many violations that walk in front of me every time I enter Norrath that I find it annoying that some feel the need to &quot;warn&quot; me about mine. <br>
<br>
Specifically there are vast numbers of names taken from popular fantasy with barely a letter changed. <br>
<br>
Contrariwise I have seen names which violate the above policy but sit very well on the character. One dwarf wearing the name of a well-known dwarf NPC looked every inch the part and I would happily believe him part of that illustrious line.<br>
<br>
The saddest however are the &quot;humorous&quot; ones - what might have been fleetingly funny for a couple of levels at character creation. That character has to put up with the same weak joke forever (or spend $50).<br>
<br>
I would never petition for a name. In the recent discussions of VI failings in the CS department I can't help wondering how much better it would be if petitions were kept to real issues.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#A62A2A>- </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie>Firiona Vie</a><font color=#A62A2A> - </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4>The Soapbox</a> <font color=#A62A2A> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 7.0.8<br>Copyright ©1999-2002 ezboard, Inc.<br>Accelerated By <a href=http://www.wbs.com/ezboard.html>JXEL</a></center></body></html>  

